ariety.com/2007/legit/markets-festivals/rise-and-fall-of-the-city-of-mahagonny-1200510436/ \"Review. ''Rise and Fall of the City of Mahagonny''\"] ''Variety'', February 11, 2007</ref>\n|Begbick\n|Los Angeles Opera Revival<br />[[Grammy Award for Best Opera Recording]]<br />[[Grammy Award for Best Classical Album]]\n|-\n|2008\n|''[[Gypsy (musical)|Gypsy]]''\n|[[Rose Thompson Hovick|Rose]]\n|Broadway Revival<br />[[Tony Award for Best Actress in a Musical]]<br />[[Drama Desk Award for Outstanding Actress in a Musical]]\n|-\n|2010\n|''[[Women on the Verge of a Nervous Breakdown (musical)|Women on the Verge of a Nervous Breakdown]]''\n|Lucia\n|Original Broadway Production<br />Nominated\u2014[[Tony Award for Best Featured Actress in a Musical]]<br />Nominated\u2014[[Drama Desk Award for Outstanding Featured Actress in a Musical]]\n|-\n|2011\n|''An Evening with Patti LuPone and Mandy Patinkin''<ref>[http://www.playbill.com/production/an-evening-with-patti-lupone-and-mandy-patinkin-ethel-barrymore-theatre-vault-0000013750# ''An Evening with Patti LuPone and Mandy Patinkin''] Playbill, accessed November 20, 2019</ref>\n|Herself\n|Concert, [[Ethel Barrymore Theatre]]\n|-\n|2011\n| ''Company''<ref>[https://www.broadway.com/buzz/155199/stephen-colbert-patti-lupone-more-join-neil-patrick-harris-in-new-york-philharmonics-company/ \"Stephen Colbert, Patti LuPone & More Join Neil Patrick Harris in New York Philharmonic's \"Company\"\"] broadway.com, February 8, 2011</ref>\n| Joanne\n|[[New York Philharmonic]] Concert\n|-\n|2012\n|''[[The Anarchist (play)|The Anarchist]]'' \n|Cathy\n|Original Broadway Production\n|-\n|2015\n|''[[The Ghosts of Versailles]]''<ref>[https://www.operanews.com/Opera_News_Magazine/2015/5/Reviews/LOS_ANGELES__The_Ghosts_of_Versailles.html \"''The Ghosts of Versailles'' LAOpera\"]  ''Opera News'', February 8, 2015</ref>\n|Samira\n|Los Angeles Opera Revival\n|-\n|2015\n|''Shows For Days''<ref>Hetrick, Adam. [http://www.playbill.com/article/shows-for-days-starring-patti-lupone-and-michael-urie-plays-its-final-off-broadway-show-today-com-358859# \" ''Shows for Days'', Starring Patti LuPone and Michael Urie, Plays Its Final Off-Broadway \"Show\" Today\"] Playbill, August 23, 2015</ref>\n|Irene\n|Off-Broadway\n|-\n|2017\n|''[[War Paint (musical)|War Paint]]''\n|[[Helena Rubinstein]]\n|Original Broadway Production<br />Nominated\u2014[[Tony Award for Best Actress in a Musical]]<br />Nominated\u2014[[Drama Desk Award for Outstanding Actress in a Musical]]\n|-\n|2018\n| ''Company''<ref>Gans, Andrew. [http://www.playbill.com/article/rosalie-craig-and-patti-lupone-star-in-gender-swapped-company-opening-in-london-october-17# \"Rosalie Craig and Patti LuPone Star in Gender-Swapped ''Company'', Opening in London October 17\"] Playbill, October 17, 2018</ref>\n| Joanne\n|West End Revival<br />[[WhatsOnStage Award]] for Best Supporting Actress in a Musical<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thestage.co.uk/news/2019/whatsonstage-awards-2019-the-winners-in-full/|title=WhatsOnStage Awards 2019: the winners in full|first=Georgia|last=Snow|date=March 3, 2019|access-date=June 17, 2019|newspaper=[[The Stage]]|via=www.thestage.co.uk}}</ref><br />[[Laurence Olivier Award for Best Actress in a Supporting Role in a Musical]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://officiallondontheatre.com/olivier-awards/year/2019/|title=Winners list for the Olivier Awards 2019 with Mastercard|website=Official London Theatre|access-date=June 17, 2019|via=officiallondontheatre.com|publisher=[[Society of London Theatre]]}}</ref>\n|-\n|2020\n| ''Company''<ref>Franklin, Marc J.[http://www.playbill.com/article/meet-the-cast-of-broadways-gender-bent-revival-of-company# \"Meet the Cast of Broadway\u2019s Upcoming Revival of ''Company''\"] Playbill, October 26, 2019</ref>\n| Joanne\n|Broadway Revival\n|}\n\n===Film===\nSources: TCM<ref name=tcm>[http://www.tcm.com/tcmdb/person/117747|0/Patti-Lupone/ \"Patti LuPone Filmography\"] tcm.com, accessed November 17, 2019</ref>; AllMovie<re