any'', With Neil Patrick Harris and Patti LuPone, Airs on PBS Nov. 8\"] Playbill, November 8, 2013</ref>\n| Joanne\n| Taped version of 2011 NY Philharmonic Concert, televised on PBS [[Great Performances]]\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[Parker (2013 film)|Parker]]''\n| Ascension\n| \n|-\n| 2016\n| ''[[The Comedian (2016 film)|The Comedian]]''\n| Flo Berkowitz\n|\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''[[Cliffs of Freedom]]''\n| Yia-Yia\n| \n|-\n| 2019\n| ''[[Last Christmas (film)|Last Christmas]]''\n| Joyce\n| \n|}\n\n===Television===\nSources: TCM<ref name=tcm/>; AllMovie<ref name=all/>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\"| Notes\n|-\n| 1976\n| ''The Time of Your Life''\n| Kitty Duval\n| Television film\n|-\n| 1987\n| ''Cowboy Joe''\n| Linda Tidmunk\n| Television film\n|-\n| 1987\n| ''[[LBJ: The Early Years]]''\n| [[Lady Bird Johnson]]\n| Television film\n|-\n| 1989\u20131993\n| ''[[Life Goes On (TV series)|Life Goes On]]''\n| Elizabeth \"Libby\" Thatcher\n| 83 episodes<br />Nominated\u2014[[Viewers for Quality Television|Viewers for Quality Television Award for Best Actress in a Quality Drama Series]] <small>(1990\u201391)</small>\n|-\n| 1992\n| ''[[The Water Engine (film)|The Water Engine]]''\n| Rita Lang\n| Television film\n|-\n| 1993\n| ''[[Frasier]]''\n| Pam (voice)\n| Episode: \"Dinner at Eight\"\n|-\n| 1995\n| ''The Song Spinner''\n| Zantalalia\n| Television film<br />Nominated\u2014[[Daytime Emmy Awards|Daytime Emmy Award for Outstanding Performer in a Children's Special]]\n|-\n| 1996\n| ''[[Remember WENN]]''\n| Grace Cavendish\n| Episode: \"There But for the Grace\"\n|-\n| 1996\u20131997\n| ''[[Law & Order]]''\n| Ruth Miller\n| 2 episodes\n|-\n| 1998\n| ''Frasier''\n| Aunt [[Zora Crane]]\n| Episode: \"[[Beware of Greeks (Frasier)|Beware of Greeks]]\"<br />Nominated\u2014[[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Guest Actress in a Comedy Series]]\n|-\n| 1999\n| ''[[Encore! Encore!]]''\n| Wine critic\n| Episode: \"A Review to Remember\"\n|-\n| 20